Log- 1:
    - generate jar file from spring initializer with web dependencies needed for the project.
    - unzip the file and open it through IDE.
    - check everything is set properly in pom file.
    - in the application.properties, specify the properties that connect to the database (PostgreSQL).

Log- 2:
    - Create a controller service with required annotations, (RestController, GetMapping, RequestMapping)
    - architecture ->
    Client -> Controller_Layer -> Service_Layer -> DAO -> Database.
    - Client sends a request that is processed in the controller layer. Service layer consists of Business Logic. DAO layer connects to database.
    - getting data from service layer and returning to client => create a service class